{"title_page": "That's My Baby (1926 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1926 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = That's My Baby\n| image          = That's My Baby (1926 film).jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[William Beaudine]]\n| producer       = [[Adolph Zukor]]<br>[[Jesse Lasky]]\n| writer         = [[Wade Boteler]]<br>[[George Crone]] <br> [[Tay Garnett]]\n| starring       = [[Douglas MacLean]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Jack MacKenzie\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = [[Paramount Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|1926|4|19}}\n| runtime        = 70 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent\n}}\n\n'''''That's My Baby''''' is a 1926 American [[silent film|silent]] [[comedy film]] directed by [[William Beaudine]].<ref name=\"SilentEra\">{{cite web |url=http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/T/ThatsMyBaby1926.html |title=That's My Baby |accessdate=December 14, 2013 |work=Silent Era}}</ref> A surviving copy is preserved in a European archive, Paris.<ref>[http://lcweb2.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.97/default.html The Library of Congress American Silent Feature Film Survival Catalog: ''That's My Baby'']</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Douglas MacLean]] as Alan Boyd\n* [[Margaret Morris (actress)|Margaret Morris]] as Helen Raynor\n* [[Claude Gillingwater]] as John Raynor\n* [[Eugenie Forde]] as Mrs. John Raynor\n* [[Wade Boteler]] as Dave Barton\n* [[Richard Tucker (actor)|Richard Tucker]] as Schuyler Van Loon\n* [[Fred Kelsey]] as Murphy\n* [[Harry Earles]] as The Baby\n* [[William Orlamond]] as Drug Clerk\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0017458|That's My Baby}}\n\n{{William Beaudine |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:That's My Baby}}\n[[Category:1926 films]]\n[[Category:1926 comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American comedy films]]\n[[Category:American silent feature films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by William Beaudine]]\n{{1920s-comedy-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1926 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = That's My Baby\n| image          = That's My Baby (1926 film).jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[William Beaudine]]\n| producer       = [[Adolph Zukor]]<br>[[Jesse Lasky]]\n| writer         = [[Wade Boteler]]<br>[[George Crone]] <br> [[Tay Garnett]]\n| starring       = [[Douglas MacLean]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Jack MacKenzie\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = [[Paramount Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|1926|4|19}}\n| runtime        = 70 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent\n}}\n\n'''''That's My Baby''''' is a 1926 American [[silent film|silent]] [[comedy film]] directed by [[William Beaudine]].<ref name=\"SilentEra\">{{cite web |url=http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/T/ThatsMyBaby1926.html |title=That's My Baby |accessdate=14 December 2013 |work=Silent Era}}</ref> A surviving copy is preserved in a European archive, Paris.<ref>[http://lcweb2.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.97/default.html The Library of Congress American Silent Feature Film Survival Catalog: ''That's My Baby'']</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Douglas MacLean]] as Alan Boyd\n* [[Margaret Morris (actress)|Margaret Morris]] as Helen Raynor\n* [[Claude Gillingwater]] as John Raynor\n* [[Eugenie Forde]] as Mrs. John Raynor\n* [[Wade Boteler]] as Dave Barton\n* [[Richard Tucker (actor)|Richard Tucker]] as Schuyler Van Loon\n* [[Fred Kelsey]] as Murphy\n* [[Harry Earles]] as The Baby\n* [[William Orlamond]] as Drug Clerk\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0017458|That's My Baby}}\n\n{{William Beaudine |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:That's My Baby}}\n[[Category:1926 films]]\n[[Category:1926 comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American comedy films]]\n[[Category:American silent feature films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by William Beaudine]]\n{{1920s-comedy-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/That%27s_My_Baby_(1926_film)"}
